LORENE:
Instructions are the same as GP. Use the local_settings in this directory.

FUKA:
Follow instructions here: https://samueltootle.github.io/fuka/index.html

Use provided CmakeLocal.cmake config file.

When building the ETK with Kadath thorns, you may run into a strange bug when reading initial data. This could be caused by the order in which libraries are linked. Run:

gmake [config name] SILENT=NO -j28 2>&1 | tee gmake_out

and modify the link command at the end. Move -mkl to the end of the command and run the link command yourself.

To use FUKA with simfactory, I needed to compile with this particular order of operations:
1) run ./simfactory/bin/sim build
2) delete the executable
3) run the gmake command above
4) manually link as detailed above

General process for generating ID on Frontera:
FUKA tends to crash when trying to generate res=13 data from the beginning.
1) Make sure COs directory is empty.
2) Run res = 11 par file. One successful run used 32 nodes, 28 OMP threads per node, ~8 hrs
3) Use BNS_TOTAL...info/dat (and this file only!!!) as new starting point (eg. rename to initbin.info/dat) 
4) Change initial_resolution to 11. Change res to 13. Change sequence controls as necessary.
5) Run res = 13 par file. One successful run used 32 nodes, 28 OMP threads per node, ~15 hrs.
